race.comment: WHO'S YOUR MAMA (1) brought good overall form from Carnarvon but was plain placing distantly at Lenora last time. She's better than that and may appreciate coming back to 1400m. Too good for these at best. IMA WILD GIRL (4) spiked her figures beaten 2L behind Dublin Red over 1200m at Lenora. Will go close holding that form. ROEY CLAM (3) finished 3.7 lengths away in the same contest after being in the firing line on the bend. Is a solid top-three chance. OUR KIWI PRINCESS (2) comes out of that race as well and wasn't too far away. Has an inside gate today and keeps the 3kg claim. Deserves consideration.
